snippet: Maze beat Frida Hansdotter by 0.34 in a women’s World Cup slalom race in Levi, Finland, on Saturday, and the defending world champion Mikaela Shiffrin finished 11th.
abstract: Tina Maze of Slovenia wins women’s World Cup slalom season opener with an overall time of 1 minute 55.15 seconds.
lead_paragraph: Maze beat Frida Hansdotter by 0.34 in a women’s World Cup slalom race in Levi, Finland, on Saturday, and the defending world champion Mikaela Shiffrin finished 11th.

headline.main: Tina Maze Wins Opening Slalom Race; Mikaela Shiffrin Is 11th
